== Applications ==

=== Matrix functions ===

Three of the most fundamental operations which can be performed on square matrices are matrix addition, multiplication by a scalar, and matrix multiplication. These are exactly those operations necessary for defining a polynomial function of an &quot;n&quot; × &quot;n&quot; matrix formula_2. If we recall from basic calculus that many functions can be written as a Maclaurin series, then we can define more general functions of matrices quite easily. If formula_2 is diagonalizable, that is

:formula_296

with

:formula_297

then

:formula_298

and the evaluation of the Maclaurin series for functions of formula_2 is greatly simplified. For example, to obtain any power &quot;k&quot; of formula_2, we need only compute formula_301, premultiply formula_301 by formula_47, and postmultiply the result by formula_304.

Using generalized eigenvectors, we can obtain the Jordan normal form for formula_2 and these results can be generalized to a straightforward method for computing functions of nondiagonalizable matrices. (See Matrix function#Jordan decomposition.)

